---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy" description="Privacy Policy for modrzejewski.it, including contact form processing and Cloudflare Web Analytics usage.">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> March 12, 2026</p>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how data is handled when you use <strong>modrzejewski.it</strong>.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
      <p>
        Website owner: Dominik Modrzejewski.<br />
        Contact: via the contact form on this website or LinkedIn profile linked in the footer.
      </p>

      <h2>2. What Data Is Collected</h2>
      <p>If you submit the contact form, the following data may be processed:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Full name</li>
        <li>Email address</li>
        <li>Subject (optional)</li>
        <li>Message content</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. How Contact Form Data Is Processed</h2>
      <p>
        The contact form is processed via <strong>FormSubmit</strong> (third-party form processing service).
        Submitted form data is sent to FormSubmit to deliver your message.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Technical and Anti-Spam Data</h2>
      <p>
        To protect the contact form against abuse, technical anti-spam signals are used (for example hidden bot-trap fields,
        timing checks, and short cooldowns between repeated submissions).
      </p>

      <h2>5. Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        This website uses <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> for high-level traffic measurement.
        No advertising trackers are used.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Local Storage</h2>
      <p>This website uses browser local storage for functional purposes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Theme preference (light/dark mode)</li>
        <li>Temporary contact form cooldown state</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Legal Basis (GDPR)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Contact form processing: legitimate interest and/or pre-contractual communication.</li>
        <li>Website security and anti-spam controls: legitimate interest.</li>
        <li>Functional local storage: legitimate interest (site operation and UX).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>8. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        Contact inquiries are retained only as long as reasonably necessary to handle communication, follow-up,
        and legal/administrative obligations.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights to request access, correction, deletion,
        restriction, objection, or data portability.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>
        This site contains links to third-party websites (for example LinkedIn, GitHub, Trailhead).
        Their privacy practices are governed by their own policies.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        This policy may be updated from time to time to reflect legal or technical changes.
        The latest version is always published on this page.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
